### Build-a-Bank · Step 21 · Payments — Saga (compensation) + Redis Idempotency-Key + DLQ
### Start (see Step 20 for the broker; Step 21 adds Redis):
### 0) Redis:   docker run -d --name bank-redis -p 6379:6379 redis:7.4-alpine
### 1) Auth:    ./mvnw -pl services/auth spring-boot:run                                           # 8083
### 2) Postgres:docker compose -f services/demand-account/compose.yaml up -d                       # 5433
### 3) demand-account: SPRING_DATASOURCE_URL=jdbc:postgresql://localhost:5433/demand_account \
###                    AUTH_JWKS_URI=http://localhost:8083/oauth2/jwks REDIS_HOST=localhost \
###                    ./mvnw -pl services/demand-account spring-boot:run                          # 8082

@auth = http://localhost:8083
@da   = http://localhost:8082

### Log in for a token (paste the JWT below).
POST {{auth}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{"username":"alice","password":"password"}

@token = PASTE_JWT_HERE

### Open two accounts.
POST {{da}}/api/accounts
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{"accountNumber":"ACC-A","currency":"USD","openingBalance":200.00}

###
POST {{da}}/api/accounts
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{"accountNumber":"ACC-B","currency":"USD","openingBalance":0.00}

### A) Pay A → B (Saga: debit then credit, each its own committed step) → 200 {"paymentId":...}
POST {{da}}/api/v1/payments
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Idempotency-Key: PAY-001
Content-Type: application/json

{"from":"ACC-A","to":"ACC-B","amount":40.00}

### B) RETRY with the SAME Idempotency-Key → returns the SAME paymentId, money moves ONCE (Redis idempotency).
POST {{da}}/api/v1/payments
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Idempotency-Key: PAY-001
Content-Type: application/json

{"from":"ACC-A","to":"ACC-B","amount":40.00}

### C) COMPENSATION: pay to a non-existent account → the debit commits, the credit fails, the Saga refunds the
### source, and you get 422 application/problem+json {"title":"Payment failed",...}. Check ACC-A — its balance
### is unchanged (debited then refunded). No money is lost or created.
POST {{da}}/api/v1/payments
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: application/json

{"from":"ACC-A","to":"ACC-NOPE","amount":25.00}

### D) Confirm ACC-A is consistent after the compensated payment.
GET {{da}}/api/accounts/ACC-A
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
